{
  "stem": "22047.3",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "He fired a shot and hit the last guy in line behind this tank.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "What a shot.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "[LAUGHS] But we spent three days on this line fighting off attacks by the Germans.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "One night, a tank came up on our position, and they didn't know where we were, and started firing his gun.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "And because he didn't know, he kind of backed off.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "We were surrounded, I'm told, five times by the German military.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "But our patrols would come up and break through, and they'd-- they'd retreat.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 40,
      "text": "And finally, we were given the order to come back to the main line, because they had it finally organized so that we didn't have to continue to fight.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 41,
      "text": "You're only supposed to be on an outpost for a few hours.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 42,
      "text": "You don't have the firepower that's back behind you.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 43,
      "text": "We were five miles in front of the main line.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 44,
      "text": "Well, we came back, and we got back at night and spent that night on the side of a hill.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 45,
      "text": "And it snowed and it snowed and it snowed.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 46,
      "text": "And fortunately, we had blankets and sleeping bags.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 47,
      "text": "And-- but I got up the next morning, I couldn't find anybody.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 48,
      "text": "Everybody was under snow.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 49,
      "text": "So I had to go around and help uncover my guys.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 50,
      "text": "And then we were moved from there and quartered in a fort on the Maginot Line, which was near a little town called Ingersheim.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 51,
      "text": "Our battalion was in a place called Schonenberg behind this town.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 52,
      "text": "And then we were in this fort out near-- out in front of-- of the little town of Ingersheim.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 53,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] And we spent many an hour in this fort.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 54,
      "text": "And the rest of the time we would go out and dig foxholes to-- to prevent attacks by the Germans.",
      "word_count": 20
    }
  ],
